The paper deals with the detection of DDoS attacks, which is a common problem in computer security (cs.CR). The method proposed involves analyzing network traffic, which falls under the category of network security (cs.NI). The paper also uses an exponential moving average algorithm for decision-making, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing time series data, which is a common topic in signal processing and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves testing and comparing the performance of different detection methods, which is a common topic in data analysis and machine learning (cs.DS).
